  "wikitext": "{{Navbutton/Separation}}\n{{Object Infobox\n|image = Nitre Dropped.png\n|icon = Nitre.png\n|foodType =[[Elemental]] [[File:Elemental.png|32px|link=Elemental]]<br>[[Food_Type/DST#Nitre|Nitre]] [[File:Nitre.png|32px|link=Food_Type/DST#Nitre]]<br>(non-survivor food)\n|craft_desctiption = ''Transmute Gold Nugget into a Nitre.''\n|hpRestored = 10\n|burnTime = [[File:Nitre.png|32px|link=Fuel/DST#Nitre Fuel]] 1.5 min.\n|hungerRestored = 2\n|sanityRestored = 0\n|stack = 40\n|droppedBy = {{pic|32|Boulder}} ({{pic|24|Pickaxe}}) [[Earthquake]] (20%)<br>\n{{pic|32|Burrow}} ({{pic|24|Shovel}}) (20%) <br>{{pic|24|Petrified Tree}} {{pic|24|Nitre Formation}} ({{pic|24|Pickaxe}})\n|spawnCode = \"nitre\"\n|filter = {{Pic32|Wilson Filter}}\n|ingredient1 = Gold Nugget\n|multiplier1 = 2 ({{Pic|28|Wilson Portrait|Wilson}} only)\n|skill = Transmute Ore II\n|skillOwner = Wilson\n}}\n{{Quotes\n|wilson = I'm not a geologist.\n|willow = There are tiny explosions trapped inside.\n|wolfgang = Is rock, but different.\n|wendy = Herein lies the folly of man.\n|wx78 = SOME ROCKS ARE BETTER THAN OTHERS\n|wickerbottom = Also known as saltpeter.\n|woodie = It's how we built the railway.\n|maxwell = One third of the way there...\n|wagstaff = A magnificent mineral with endothermic properties!\n|wigfrid = It cöntains explösive cömpönents.\n|webber = What are we supposed to do with this?\n|walani = Not just any old dumb rock.\n|warly = How curious.\n|woodlegs = Cannon food thet be.\n|wilba = ALL THAT GLITTERS 'TIS GOLD!\n|wormwood = Pow Rock\n|wurt = Funny rock.\n|wheeler = It's not gold, but it's not useless.\n|winona = I got some plans in mind for that.\n|wortox = I've no earthly clue how to use this.\n|walter = Nitre here nor there. Heh...\n|wanda = A rock of some sort.\n|choose = wolfgang}}\n'''Nitre''' is a [[:Category:Minerals|Mineral]] resource obtained by mining smooth [[Boulders]], which will drop at least one (along with other minerals) upon being mined. It also occasionally falls during [[Caves|underground]] [[Earthquake]]s. It can be used to craft [[Salt Lick]]s and [[Gunpowder]].\n\nIt can be used to make [[Endothermic Fire]]s, [[Endothermic Fire#Endothermic Fire Pit|Endothermic Fire Pits]] and the [[Morning Star]]. Endothermic Fires can also be refueled with Nitre. Nitre can also be obtained by [[Shovel|digging]] up a [[Moleworm]]'s [[Burrow]]. It can be used as a fuel for [[Ice Flingomatic|Ice Flingomatics]] to refuel 19%.\n\nNitre is additionally dropped by [[Petrified Tree|Petrified Evergreens]] and used to craft [[Booster Shot|Booster Shots]], [[Flare|Flares]] and [[Bath Bomb|Bath Bombs]]. [[Winona]] uses Nitre both to craft her [[Winona's Generator|Generator]] and to refuel it, while [[Warly]] can craft [[Chef Pouch]]es from it.\n\nNitre can also be crafted by [[Wilson]] if he has the \"[[Transmute Ore II]]\" ability from his insight skill-tree.\n\n=={{pic32|Icon Tools}} Usage==\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Nitre\n|item2 = Twigs\n|item3 = Cut Grass\n|result = Flare}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Nitre\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Cut Grass\n|count2 = 3\n|tool = Science Machine\n|result = Endothermic Fire}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Nitre\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Cut Stone\n|count2 = 4\n|item3 = Electrical Doodad\n|count3 = 2\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Endothermic Fire Pit}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Nitre/DST\n|count1 = 3\n|item2 = Heat Gland\n|count2 = 2\n|item3 = Twigs/DST\n|count3 = 4\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Ardent Axe\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Nitre/DST\n|count1 = 3\n|item2 = Heat Gland\n|count2 = 2\n|item3 = Twigs/DST\n|count3 = 4\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Pyretic Pickaxe\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Nitre/DST\n|count1 = 3\n|item2 = Heat Gland\n|count2 = 2\n|item3 = Twigs/DST\n|count3 = 4\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Searing Shovel\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Nitre/DST\n|count1 = 3\n|item2 = Heat Gland\n|count2 = 2\n|item3 = Twigs/DST\n|count3 = 4\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Hotheaded Hammer\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Nitre/DST\n|count1 = 3\n|item2 = Heat Gland\n|count2 = 2\n|item3 = Twigs/DST\n|count3 = 4\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Heated Garden Hoe\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Nitre/DST\n|count1 = 4\n|item2 = Heat Gland\n|count2 = 2\n|item3 = Flint/DST\n|count3 = 4\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Coals\n|resultcount = 4\n}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Nitre\n|count1 = 4\n|item2 = Boards\n|count2 = 2\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Salt Lick}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Nitre\n|item2 = Charcoal\n|item3 = Rotten Egg\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Gunpowder}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Nitre\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Electrical Doodad\n|count2 = 2\n|item3 = Volt Goat Horn\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Morning Star}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Nitre\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Rot\n|count2 = 8\n|item3 = Stinger\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Booster Shot}}\n{{Recipe\n|item2 = Healing Salve\n|count2 = 1\n|item1 = Nitre\n|count1 = 1\n|item3 = Marble\n|count3 = 1\n|item4 = Slurtle Slime\n|count4 = 1\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Slimy Salve}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Nitre\n|item2 = Lune Tree Blossom\n|tool = Celestial Orb\n|result = Bath Bomb\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Nitre\n|item2 = Rocks\n|count2 = 2\n|item3 = Salt Crystals\n|result = Collected Dust\n|tool = Blueprint (rare)}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Nitre\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Twigs\n|count2 = 4\n|item3 = Cut Grass\n|count3 = 4\n|result = Chef Pouch\n|character = Warly}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Nitre\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Trusty Tape\n|item3 = Log\n|count3 = 2\n|result = Winona's Generator\n|character = Winona}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Nitre\n|count1 = 4\n|item2 = Monster Meat\n|count2 = 1\n|item3 = Silk\n|count3 = 2\n|result = Spitter Switcherdoodle\n|character = Webber}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Nitre\n|count1 = 3\n|result = Gold Nugget\n|resultcount = 1\n|character = Wilson\n|skill = Transmute Ore II}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Rot\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Nitre\n|item3 = Manure\n|count3 = 5\n|result = Compost Wrap\n|character = Wormwood}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Nitre\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Mosquito Sack\n|count2 = 1\n|item3 = Manure\n|count3 = 1\n|result = Fertilizzzer\n|character = Wurt\n|skill = Itchcraft I}}\n\n=={{pic32|Placeholder}} Trivia==\n* Nitre was added in the ''[[Version History#March 12, 2013 - A Little Rain Must Fall|A Little Rain Must Fall]]'' update.\n* Nitre was changed to be dropped by the small, smooth boulder in ''[[Version History#April 20, 2013 - The End of the Beginning.5B3.5D|The End of the Beginning]]'' update.\n* Nitre, a.k.a. Saltpeter (Potassium Nitrate, KNO₃), is a common ingredient in creating gunpowder in the real world. It is also an ingredient in fertilizer. Although it cannot be directly used as fertilizer in game, it can be used to craft [[Compost Wrap]], which can be used as fertilizer in ''[[Don't Starve Together]]''.\n<tabber>\nResources=\n{{Resources}}\n|-|\nCraftable Items=\n{{Craftable Items and Structures on DST}}\n|-|\nFood=\n{{Food}}\n</tabber>\n[[vi:Tiêu Thạch]]\n[[Category:Resources]]\n[[Category:Minerals]]\n[[Category:Items]]\n[[Category:Non-Flammable]]\n[[Category:Fuel]]"
